Colombian Stock Movers: Avianca Taca Holding, Almacenes Exito

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-09-28T21:07:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-28/colombian-stock-movers-avianca-taca-holding-almacenes-exito.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index fell 0.7 percent to 12,878.30 while the
Colcap Index declined 0.4 percent to 1,586.55.  Almacenes Exito SA (EXITO)  ,  Colombia ’s biggest publicly
traded retailer, rose 0.4 percent to 22,900 pesos. The company
said yesterday it sold 2.5 trillion pesos ($1.3 billion) worth
of shares. Exito had orders for 196.05 million shares and sold
114.27 million, the company said in a regulatory filing
yesterday.  Avianca Taca Holding SA (PFAVTA CB), the owner of
Colombia’s largest airline, rose 1.6 percent to 4,575 pesos.  The company will pay about $500 million for four Airbus SAS
cargo planes as the owner of Colombia’s largest airline by sales
positions itself for a U.S. approval of a free trade accord with
the South American nation, Chief Executive Officer Fabio Villegas told reporters yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
 bschmidt16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
